# Walkthrough: Stripe → Razorpay Migration

## Summary
Successfully migrated the payment gateway from **Stripe** to **Razorpay** across the entire Django e-commerce project. The checkout flow now uses Razorpay's inline payment modal instead of Stripe's redirect-based checkout.

## Files Changed

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/requirements.txt) | `stripe` → [razorpay](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/utils.py#48-66) |
| [requirements-docker.txt](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/requirements-docker.txt) | `stripe` → [razorpay](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/utils.py#48-66) |
| [.env](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/.env) | Stripe keys → Razorpay key placeholders |
| [settings.py](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/config/ecommerce/settings.py) | `STRIPE_*` → `RAZORPAY_*` settings |
| [docker-compose.yml](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/docker-compose.yml) | Stripe env vars → Razorpay env vars |
| [models.py](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/models.py) | `stripe_payment_intent` → `razorpay_payment_id` |
| [utils.py](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/utils.py) | Full rewrite: Razorpay order creation + signature verification |
| [views.py](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/views.py) | Checkout + payment_success rewritten for Razorpay flow |
| [admin.py](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/admin.py) | All `stripe_payment_intent` refs → `razorpay_payment_id` |
| [checkout.html](file:///c:/Users/dhruv/E-commerce-website-master-final/apps/store/templates/store/checkout.html) | Added Razorpay JS SDK, hidden form for payment callback |

## New Payment Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Checkout Page
    participant Django Server
    participant Razorpay API

    User->>Checkout Page: Fill form & click "Proceed to Payment"
    Checkout Page->>Django Server: POST form data
    Django Server->>Razorpay API: Create Razorpay Order
    Razorpay API-->>Django Server: Return order_id
    Django Server-->>Checkout Page: Render page with order_id
    Checkout Page->>User: Open Razorpay payment modal
    User->>Razorpay API: Complete payment in modal
    Razorpay API-->>Checkout Page: Return payment_id + signature
    Checkout Page->>Django Server: POST payment data
    Django Server->>Razorpay API: Verify signature
    Django Server-->>User: Show order success page
```

